We shouldn't catch arbitrary checked exceptions. This should probably just be PrestoException.
Why do we want to ignore errors when dropping the storage table? It seems like we should log a warning, at a minimum.
catch (PrestoException e) {
    log.warn(e, "Failed to drop storage table '%s' for materialized view '%s', storageTableName, viewName);
}

